---
import ServiceLayout from '../layouts/ServiceLayout.astro';
import { pages } from '../config';

const page = pages.services.furnitureAssembly;
---

<ServiceLayout
  title={page.title}
  description={page.description}
  keyword={page.keyword}
  serviceSlug={page.slug}
>
  <fragment slot="intro">
    IKEA, store-bought, and flat-pack furniture. TV mounting, shelving installation, bed assembly. We handle it fast and clean up after.
  </fragment>

  ## What We Assemble

  **Flat-pack furniture** — IKEA, Wayfair, Amazon, and other retailers ship flat and require assembly. Bookcases, desks, dressers, kitchen islands. Most jobs take 1–3 hours depending on complexity.

  **Beds and mattress frames** — Platform beds, bed frames with storage, adjustable beds. We assemble, level, and ensure it's sturdy.

  **Entertainment units and TV stands** — Wall units, media consoles, cable management. We assemble and cable-dress the whole setup.

  **Shelving and storage** — Wall shelves, closet organizers, garage shelving. We locate studs, install brackets properly, and ensure shelves are level.

  **Desks and work tables** — Standing desks, office desks, craft tables. We assemble and check stability.

  **Outdoor furniture** — Patio sets, deck chairs, grills. We weatherproof fasteners if needed.

  ## TV Mounting

  We mount flat-screens to walls (drywall or concrete), hide cables, and set up TV stands. We locate studs, use the right brackets for weight, and ensure the TV is level and at a comfortable viewing angle.

  - TVs up to 50": $150–$300 (wall mount and cable management)
  - TVs 50"+: $250–$400 (heavier brackets, more hardware)
  - Soundbar installation: $75–$150
  - Full A/V setup (amplifier, receiver, streaming device): $300–$600

  We use stud finders and levels. We don't guess and hope—we verify everything is secure before leaving.

  ## What's Included

  - Assembly per instructions
  - Hardware tightened and double-checked
  - Debris removal and recycling of packaging
  - Leveling and stability check
  - Quick instruction on adjustment or features

  ## What's NOT Included

  - Custom modifications (cutting, drilling, painting—we'll quote separately if needed)
  - Plumbing or electrical work
  - Load-bearing shelves (walls must be verified structurally sound)

  ## Cost & Timeline

  Simple furniture (chairs, small tables): $50–$150
  Medium complexity (desks, bookcases): $150–$350
  Complex (wall units, entertainment centers): $300–$700
  TV mounting: $150–$400

  Most jobs take 1–3 hours on-site.

  ## Why Hire a Pro

  Assembly is tedious and error-prone. Instructions assume you have tools and space. Beds assembled incorrectly are a safety risk. TVs mounted wrong can fall. We've assembled hundreds of pieces—we know shortcuts, spot missing parts early, and catch assembly mistakes before you find them when the shelf collapses.

